<h2>In a Nutshell</h2>
<p>
<strong>OpenGuides&trade;</strong> is a network of free, community-maintained "wiki" city guides
to which anyone can contribute. See our <a href="/page/information">project
information</a> for more.
</p>
<h2>Technology</h2>
<p>
We have custom-developed our own software platform. Please see the <a
href="/page/software">software information</a> section for more details.
</p>
<p>
<img src="/img/rdf_icon_small.png" width="24" height="26" alt="RDF"
style="float: left; border: 1px solid #000; margin-right: 10px;">
Our technical policy is to provide the maximum possible amount of <a
href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metadata">metadata</a> about things in our guides in 
<a href="http://www.w3.org/RDF/"><acronym title="Resource Description Framework">RDF</acronym></a>,
in order to facilitate integration into other systems.
</p>
<h2>Contributors Needed</h2>
<p>
The OpenGuides network needs you! We are always looking for more cities to
add to our collection of guides. If your town isn't represented here, you
can <a href="/page/software">set up a guide</a> yourself and join us.
</p>
<p>
Contact us by <a href="mailto:openguides-dev@openguides.org">mailing the
developers</a>, joining the <a href="/page/lists">mailing list</a> or
talking to us on <acronym title="Internet Relay Chat"><a href="/page/irc">IRC</a></acronym>.
</p>
